{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"agent_message","text":"The canvas is a 10×10 target-composition puzzle. The useful dense measure is exact target-cell matches (0 initially): applying a stamp paints a deterministic half-plane mask, and moving the vessel changes that mask (top half, side half, or a diagonal). Palette clicks only change paint color. I’ve verified these effects across multiple colors and positions; next I’m enumerating the small vessel-position graph and searching compositions against the 100-cell target."}}
